Introduction¶

In this project I have choosed the TMDb move data, this data set contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue. Certain columns, like ‘cast’ and ‘genres’, contain multiple values separated by pipe (|) characters. And this will require a special handling to get more valuable data from it.

Questions that I intended to explore in this data set are¶

1. What kind of properties are associated with movies that have high profit?

  • Does movie popularity have an effect on profit?
  • Does movie release year have an effect on profit?
  • Does movie release month have an effect on profit?
  • Does movie runtime have an effect on profit?
  • Does movie adjusted budget have an effect on profit?
  • Does movie genre have an effect on profit?

2. Which movies generes are most popular from year to year?

In [395]:
# get the release month from data
movies_df['release_date'] = movies_df['release_date'].dt.month
genres_df['release_date'] = genres_df['release_date'].dt.month

# change columns type
movies_df['budget_adj'] = movies_df['budget_adj'].astype(int)
genres_df['budget_adj'] = genres_df['budget_adj'].astype(int)
movies_df['revenue_adj'] = movies_df['revenue_adj'].astype(int)
genres_df['revenue_adj'] = genres_df['revenue_adj'].astype(int)

movies_df['Profit'] = movies_df['Profit'].astype(int)
genres_df['Profit'] = genres_df['Profit'].astype(int)

# rename columns type
movies_df.rename(columns={'release_date':'Months'}, inplace=True)
genres_df.rename(columns={'release_date':'Months'}, inplace=True)
movies_df.rename(columns={'budget_adj':'Budget'}, inplace=True)
genres_df.rename(columns={'budget_adj':'Budget'}, inplace=True)
movies_df.rename(columns={'revenue_adj':'Revenue'}, inplace=True)
genres_df.rename(columns={'revenue_adj':'Revenue'}, inplace=True)
movies_df.rename(columns={'release_year':'Year'}, inplace=True)
genres_df.rename(columns={'release_year':'Year'}, inplace=True)
movies_df.rename(columns={'original_title':'Title'}, inplace=True)
genres_df.rename(columns={'original_title':'Title'}, inplace=True)

Conclusions¶

We can sum up our findings as follow:¶

  • Most profitable movies are released on summer and new year
  • Movies with genres "Action|Adventure|Fantasy|Science Fiction" was most profitable movies.
  • Popularity does not the main factor on movies profitability
  • The budget affects the profit by a major factor and this affect the movie quality
  • Most released movies genre is Dram, but it loses its interest over time and Actions becomes more dominate on last period

There was a missing data and we drpoed them and this affect the analysis for the data set
